            <personal-details:content>Dr. Qian Gong has over 30 years of optical system experience.  She has worked on many NASA flight projects, such as, Hubble Space Telescope (HST), James Web Space Telescope (JWST), Wide Field InfraRed Survey Telescope (WFIRST), Sun Earth Connection Coronal and Heliospheric Investigation (SECCHI/STEREO), Far Ultraviolet Spectroscopic Explorer (FUSE), Composite IntraRed Spectrometer (CIRS), Moderate Resolution Imaging Spectrora-diometer (MODIS), etc.  She also provided the optical designs for a number of proposals.  Some proposals, such as Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS) and Prototype Imaging Spectrograph for Coronagraphic Exoplanet Studies (PISCES), have been awarded and became instruments for flight missions.  She had performed different functions as optics lead, system engineer, optical designer, analysts, and alignment and testing engineer.  

Dr. Qian Gong was an optical lead for SECCHI COR2 instrument.  Technically, she conducted optical design, analysis, alignment and testing.  She is also a system and optics lead for PISCES.  She also led the WFIRST prototype wide field slitless spectrometer design and de-velopment.  Both PISCES and spectrometer have baselined as flight WFIRST instrument.
 
Currently, she is involved in number of GSFC flight projects and proposal activities, incluing WFIRST, Large UV/Optical/Infrared Surveyor LUVOIR, Balloon-borne Investigation of Temperature and Speed of Electrons in the corona (BITSE), and a number of proposals.</personal-details:content>
